Definition
----------

*inconsistency-introduction-1* is the :ref:`inference-rule<inference_rule_math_concept>`:

.. math::

   \left( \mathbf{P}, \neg \left(\mathbf{P}\right) \right) \vdash Inc\left(\mathcal{T}\right)

In straightforward language, if we prove a proposition and its negation, it follows that the theory is inconsistent.